title: RSNA Intracranial: Simple DenseNet in Keras
description: About this kernelIn this kernel, I go through each steps of the process for building a multi-label classifier in the RSNA Intracranial Hemorrhage competition. I will be only using a subset of the total dataset. Notes V7: I noticed that it takes roughly 1000 seconds to run 2000 iterations. Therefore, I set each batch to be 2000 iterations, so that we can estimate the total running time to be a multiple of 1000 seconds (and at every slice of 2000 iterations, we can get the validation results).
